{
  "video_id": "3dxbQQPftuE",
  "title": "The Dark Origins of the Game of Life",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 847.0,
      "end_time": 4700.0,
      "text": "- [Narrator] Without Abraham Lincoln, and really his beard,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 4700.0,
      "end_time": 6870.0,
      "text": "Milton Bradley, the godfather of board games"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6870.0,
      "end_time": 8937.0,
      "text": "would have never existed."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 8937.0,
      "end_time": 11465.0,
      "text": "Bold statement, I know, but let me explain."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 11465.0,
      "end_time": 14480.0,
      "text": "(upbeat music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 15259.0,
      "end_time": 16676.0,
      "text": "The Game of Life."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 18000.0,
      "end_time": 20746.0,
      "text": "The spinner, the cars, the choices,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 20746.0,
      "end_time": 24768.0,
      "text": "college or career, kids or no kids, lawyer or farmer."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 24768.0,
      "end_time": 28778.0,
      "text": "This family game night staple was once a pretty morbid game."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 28778.0,
      "end_time": 31430.0,
      "text": "Back in the 1800s, Milton Bradley was"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 31431.0,
      "end_time": 33476.0,
      "text": "in the lithograph business."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 33476.0,
      "end_time": 36493.0,
      "text": "Following the Republican National Convention of 1860,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 36493.0,
      "end_time": 38986.0,
      "text": "Bradley printed thousands of images of Abraham Lincoln"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 38986.0,
      "end_time": 41358.0,
      "text": "who was clean-shaven at the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 41359.0,
      "end_time": 44813.0,
      "text": "Shortly thereafter, Lincoln debuted his iconic beard,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 44813.0,
      "end_time": 48480.0,
      "text": "rendering all of Bradley&#39;s prints worthless."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 49573.0,
      "end_time": 52740.0,
      "text": "His lithograph business went belly up."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 55230.0,
      "end_time": 57421.0,
      "text": "So, Bradley was forced to try something new."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 57421.0,
      "end_time": 59900.0,
      "text": "He came up with a board game, a seemingly dark"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 59900.0,
      "end_time": 62413.0,
      "text": "and twisted board game, appropriately named"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 62413.0,
      "end_time": 64447.0,
      "text": "The Checkered Game of Life."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 64447.0,
      "end_time": 67213.0,
      "text": "The game functioned in a similar way to how it does now."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 67213.0,
      "end_time": 69512.0,
      "text": "There was a spinner, colored circles that moved"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 69512.0,
      "end_time": 71718.0,
      "text": "around the board, and of course squares"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 71718.0,
      "end_time": 73925.0,
      "text": "that could either make you or break you."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 73925.0,
      "end_time": 77300.0,
      "text": "The squares on the original game were overwhelmingly grim,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 77300.0,
      "end_time": 79523.0,
      "text": "boasting actions like disgrace, poverty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 79523.0,
      "end_time": 83363.0,
      "text": "ruin, crime, prison, and well, suicide."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 83363.0,
      "end_time": 87345.0,
      "text": "Regardless, the game flew off the shelves."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 87345.0,
      "end_time": 89472.0,
      "text": "Kids loved it and Milton Bradley went on"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 89472.0,
      "end_time": 91172.0,
      "text": "to own family game night."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 91173.0,
      "end_time": 93920.0,
      "text": "Fast forward to about a hundred years later."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 93920.0,
      "end_time": 95781.0,
      "text": "They revamped the game, trading Bradley&#39;s morbid squares"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 95781.0,
      "end_time": 99435.0,
      "text": "for the more delightful ones like payday, or graduation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 99435.0,
      "end_time": 101722.0,
      "text": "which we have all come to know and love."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 101722.0,
      "end_time": 105820.0,
      "text": "And so there you have it, the story of the game called Life."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 105820.0,
      "end_time": 106571.0,
      "text": "Thanks, Lincoln."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 106571.0,
      "end_time": 109154.0,
      "text": "(bright music)"
    }
  ]
}